<subSubSection id="87B46525FFF0FFEAFF6956D4FE532E80" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF6956D4FECE2F89" blockId="15.[189,310,1176,1202]" box="[189,310,1176,1202]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
<heading id="945981C2FFF0FFEAFF6956D4FECE2F89" bold="true" box="[189,310,1176,1202]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF6956D4FECE2F89" bold="true" box="[189,310,1176,1202]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695684FE532E80" blockId="15.[188,1399,1224,1467]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
Females of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFE9D5685FE472FD9" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[329,447,1225,1250]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juanita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFE9D5685FE472FD9" box="[329,447,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. juanita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF0FFEAFE135685FDDA2FD8" box="[455,546,1225,1251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFCD15685FC9C2FD9" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[773,868,1225,1250]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taino">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFCD15685FC9C2FD9" box="[773,868,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. taino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="AB3F4B5FFFF0FFEAFCA15684FB762FD9" author="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G." box="[885,1166,1224,1250]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" pagination="301 - 344" refId="ref12419" refString="Rheims C. A. &amp; Alayon G. 2016. Neostasina gen. nov., a new genus of huntsman spiders from the Neotropical region (Araneae, Sparassidae, Sparianthinae). Zootaxa 4079: 301 - 344. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4079.3.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Rheims &amp; Alayón 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 140−142) and 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFF6956A1FEA92E3D" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[189,337,1261,1286]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toronegro" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF6956A1FEA92E3D" box="[189,337,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. toronegro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF0FFEAFE8C56A1FE492E3C" box="[344,433,1261,1287]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFE1456A0FDE92E3C" box="[448,529,1260,1287]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="28.[189,233,849,875]" captionTargetBox="[204,1376,310,784]" captionTargetId="figure-134@28.[189,1399,286,785]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig. 16. Neostasina toronegro sp. nov., A−B: holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30719). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607956/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
A−C) by the epigyne with ar entire, recurved and MS subpentagonal. They are distinguished from both species by the spermathecae free, not encapsulated within a sclerotized structure (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFEE05778FE742E74" box="[308,396,1332,1359]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
) (encapsulated in the other species). They are additionally distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFACC5779FA8D2E75" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[1304,1397,1333,1358]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taino">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFACC5779FA8D2E75" box="[1304,1397,1333,1358]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. taino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the ar completely covering the anterior margin of MS (not covering the anterior margin in 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFADA5715FA952E49" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayon" authorityYear="2016" box="[1294,1389,1369,1394]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taino">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFADA5715FA952E49" box="[1294,1389,1369,1394]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. taino</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and from 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFEFF5731FE462EAD" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[299,446,1405,1430]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toronegro" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFEFF5731FE462EAD" box="[299,446,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. toronegro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF0FFEAFE125731FDE72EAC" box="[454,543,1405,1431]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the ar medially angled (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFF0FFEAFC835730FC492EAC" box="[855,945,1404,1431]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
) (evenly curved 
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFF0FFEAFBA65731FAFD2EAD" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[1138,1285,1405,1430]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="toronegro" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFBA65731FAFD2EAD" box="[1138,1285,1405,1430]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">N. toronegro</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFF0FFEAFAD95731FA922EAC" box="[1293,1386,1405,1431]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Males are unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
