<subSubSection id="87B46525FFF0FFF4FF695542FAFF2AD7" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="183" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF695542FEB62C13" blockId="15.[189,334,1806,1832]" box="[189,334,1806,1832]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
<heading id="945981C2FFF0FFEAFF695542FEB62C13" bold="true" box="[189,334,1806,1832]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="15" pageNumber="181" reason="3">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF695542FEB62C13" bold="true" box="[189,334,1806,1832]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF3E5572FE3F2C62" blockId="15.[189,1400,1854,2025]" box="[234,455,1854,1881]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFF0FFEAFF3E5572FEBD2C63" bold="true" box="[234,325,1854,1880]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="1015880CFFF0FFEAFE815572FE472C62" box="[341,447,1854,1881]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">holotype</typeStatus>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFF0FFEAFF69552EFA802CD2" blockId="15.[189,1400,1854,2025]" pageId="15" pageNumber="181">COLOR. Prosoma pale orange brown; cephalic region with faint brown lines extending posteriorly from PME and PLE; thoracic region with faint brown margins and scattered margins between thoracic striae; fovea brown; eye borders black. Chelicerae slightly darker than prosoma. Legs as prosoma, slightly lighter; ventrally with scattered brown spots. Palps as prosoma. Labium brown, distally pale orange,</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEFFFF5FF695345FB552A51" blockId="16.[188,1399,265,362]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">
Endites pale brownish orange, distally pale brownish yellow. Sternum pale orange brown with faint pale brown margins. Opisthosoma yellowish cream colored; dorsally with scattered irregular marks laterally and on anterior half and six median brown chevrons down posterior half (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEFFFF5FBC95303FB9A2A51" box="[1053,1122,335,362]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[190,233,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[203,1375,578,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-89@16.[189,1399,557,1913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 7. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607928/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A−B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEFFFF5FF6953DDFA8D2AF4" blockId="16.[188,1399,401,463]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">MEASUREMENTS. Total length 13.0, prosoma length 4.9, width 4.1, opisthosoma length 7.8, width 4.9. Eye diameters: 0.30, 0.25, 0.16, 0.22; interdistances: 0.25, 0.25, 0.53, 0.46, 0.21, 0.10. Legs (2143): I: 15.5</paragraph>
<caption id="9BD16626FFEFFFF5FF6A55E7FA8F2CD2" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607928" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6607928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607928/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="182" startId="16.[190,233,1963,1989]" targetBox="[203,1375,578,1901]" targetPageId="16">
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEFFFF5FF6A55E7FA8F2CD2" blockId="16.[190,1399,1963,2025]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FF6A55E7FEF62CFE" bold="true" box="[190,270,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">Fig. 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="08AE4D2DFFEFFFF5FEC255E0FE012CFE" authority="Rheims &amp; Alayón, 2022" authorityName="Rheims &amp; Alayón" authorityYear="2022" box="[278,505,1964,1989]" class="Arachnida" family="Sparassidae" genus="Neostasina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juanita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FEC255E0FE012CFE" box="[278,505,1964,1989]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">Neostasina juanita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E6E957C7FFEFFFF5FDD655E0FD9A2CFD" box="[514,610,1964,1990]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). 
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FC1455E7FC2D2CFE" bold="true" box="[960,981,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">A</emphasis>
. Habitus, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FB3B55E7FAF92CFE" bold="true" box="[1263,1281,1963,1989]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">B</emphasis>
. Habitus, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FE8D5582FE962CD3" bold="true" box="[345,366,1998,2024]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">C</emphasis>
. Epigyne, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="FDDAEABCFFEFFFF5FD5D5582FD662CD3" bold="true" box="[649,670,1998,2024]" pageId="16" pageNumber="182">D</emphasis>
. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEEFFF4FF695345FE742A7D" blockId="17.[189,1399,265,327]" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">(4.4, 2.3, 4.3, 3.6, 0.9); II: 16.2 (4.9, 2.5, 4.2, 3.7, 0.9); III: 12.9 (4.0, 2.1, 2.9, 3.0, 0.9); IV: 14.8 (4.5, 1.7, 3.5, 4.0, 1.1).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEEFFF4FF695322FC852A90" blockId="17.[187,1399,366,427]" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">
EPIGYNE. EF slightly longer than wide; MS roughly as long as wide with posterior margin rounded slightly surpassing tips of posterior projections of LL (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEEFFF4FD0F53DDFCC32A90" box="[731,827,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[190,233,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[203,1375,578,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-89@16.[189,1399,557,1913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 7. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607928/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">Figs 7C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEEFFF4FC9C53DDFC972A90" box="[840,879,401,427]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">8D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CF1136AEFFEEFFF4FF69539FFAFF2AD7" blockId="17.[189,1287,466,493]" box="[189,1287,466,493]" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">
VULVA. GP inconspicuous; SP with single anterior twist; FD postero-mediad (
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEEFFF4FB92539EFB5F2AD6" box="[1094,1191,466,493]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[190,233,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[203,1375,578,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-89@16.[189,1399,557,1913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 7. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Habitus, ventral view. C. Epigyne, ventral view. D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A−B = 2 mm; C−D = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607928" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607928/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">Figs 7D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="57952A2BFFEEFFF4FB60539EFB392AD7" box="[1204,1217,466,492]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="17.[189,231,1857,1883]" captionTargetBox="[191,1386,779,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-102@17.[189,1399,750,1807]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Fig. 8. A−C. Neostasina demaco sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MNHNPEJM). A. Epigyne, ventral view. B. Vulva, dorsal view. C. Schematic course of internal duct system. D−F. Neostasina juanita sp. nov., holotype, ♀ (MCZ 30720). D. Epigyne, ventral view. E. Vulva, dorsal view. F. Schematic course of internal duct system. Abbreviations: ar = anterior rim; CD = copulatory duct; FD = fertilization duct; GP = glandular projection; LL = lateral lobe; MS = median septum. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6607930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6607930/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="183">8</figureCitation>
E−F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
